<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-05-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-05-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="474" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d474">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Taylor</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Uhl</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">United
                                        States Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-05-31"><hi rend="italic">May 31,
                                1895</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 363.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Inclosed please find copy, with
                            translation, of a note from the minister of state informing me of the
                            release of Francisco Carrillo, in response to the demand contained in
                            your telegram of the 17th instant.</p>
                        <p>I have just sent you the following telegram: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>Minister for foreign affairs informs me that Governor-General of
                                    Cuba has ordered the release of Carrillo.</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hannis Taylor.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                        <frus:attachment>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure in No.
                                    363.—Translation.]</seg></opener>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Duke of Tetuan</gloss> to
                                    Mr. <persName type="to">Taylor</persName>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><hi rend="smallcaps">Ministry of
                                        State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <placeName type="venue"><hi rend="italic">Palace</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-05-29"><hi rend="italic">May 29,
                                    1895</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform
                                you, in reply to your polite note of the 18th instant, that I have
                                just received a telegram from the Governor-General of the Island of
                                Cuba reporting that he has ordered that the prisoner Francisco
                                Carrillo be released.</p>
                            <p>I seize, etc.,</p>
                            <closer>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">The Duke of Tetuan.</hi>
                            </closer>
                        </frus:attachment>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>